[Student "S"]
{EAST has a maximum 17 point 1NT opener.

WEST has 9 points: 
- if EAST has 15 the total is 24, not enough for game. 
- if EAST has 17 the total is 26, enough for game. 
Since WEST doesn't know what to do he passes the buck back to EAST 
by bidding 2NT; this is an invitation for EAST to bid game.

EAST has a maximum 17 point hand so she accepts the invitation.}

